2. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the performance of BCCs using belief propagation, which is a common technique in computational complexity. 
3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper mentions spatially coupled turbo-like codes (SC-TCs), which are commonly used in network coding and information networks. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of BCCs, which are commonly used in communication networks. 
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper uses weight enumerator functions and minimum distance bounds, which are common tools in data structures and algorithms.
